sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Gateway API / Proxy<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OGX as OGX Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant Auth as OIDC/OAuth2 Issuer<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant vLLM_I as vLLM Inference<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant vLLM_E as vLLM Embedding<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant VectorDB as Vector DB<br/>(Milvus/pgvector/Qdrant)

    Note over Client, VectorDB: Flow 1: Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (JWT)
    Gateway->>OGX: Forward (TLS terminated)<br/>HTTP 8321/TCP
    OGX->>Auth: Validate JWT via JWKS<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP
    Auth-->>OGX: Token valid
    OGX->>vLLM_I: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (API key)<br/>TLS (configurable)
    vLLM_I-->>OGX: Chat completion response
    OGX->>PG: Log inference (asyncpg)<br/>5432/TCP plaintext<br/>Auth: username/password
    PG-->>OGX: OK
    OGX-->>Gateway: JSON response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)

    Note over Client, VectorDB: Flow 2: RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/responses (with RAG tool)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>OGX: Forward (TLS terminated)
    OGX->>Auth: Validate JWT via JWKS
    Auth-->>OGX: Token valid
    OGX->>vLLM_E: POST /v1/embeddings<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>TLS (configurable)
    vLLM_E-->>OGX: Embedding vector
    OGX->>VectorDB: Query similar vectors<br/>Protocol varies (TCP/HTTP/gRPC)<br/>Auth: Token/password/API key
    VectorDB-->>OGX: Relevant documents
    OGX->>vLLM_I: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(with retrieved context)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    vLLM_I-->>OGX: Augmented response
    OGX->>PG: Persist state<br/>5432/TCP
    PG-->>OGX: OK
    OGX-->>Gateway: Streaming response (SSE)
    Gateway-->>Client: Streaming response

    Note over Client, VectorDB: Flow 3: File Processing

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1alpha/file-processors/process<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>Body: file content
    Gateway->>OGX: Forward (TLS terminated)
    OGX->>Auth: Validate JWT via JWKS
    Auth-->>OGX: Token valid
    Note right of OGX: In-process file processing<br/>(pypdf / docling / markitdown)
    OGX-->>Gateway: Processed file content (JSON)
    Gateway-->>Client: Response (HTTPS)
